Orange and Lemon Wafer Cookies

  --JoAnn Belack

1/2 c unsalted butter, softened
3/4 c sugar
1 large egg, room temperature
2 tsp grated orange zest
1 tsp grated lemon zest
1 tsp vanilla 
1 tsp orange extract
1 c ap flour
5 tsp cornstarch
1/4 tsp baking soda
1/4 tsp salt
Thin orange or lemon peel strips, optional

Preheat oven to 350F. In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy, 5-7 min. Beat in egg, orange zest, lemon zest and extracts. In another bowl, mix flour, cornstarch, baking soda and salt; gradually beat into creamed mixture. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2" apart onto parchment-lined baking sheets. If desired, top with orange peel strips. Bake 6-8 min or until edges are golden brown. Remove from pans to wire racks to cool.
